activities.message:
@hannanhaseeb Thanks for your report.

Have you been able to reproduce this issue in browsers other than Chrome? We've tested in Safari and using `curl` and are unable to reproduce there.

We have been able to reproduce in Chrome, however, the results we're seeing suggest that this is a browser-level issue (specifically, from the second webpage, Chrome is attempting to make the request against the disk cache and failing rather than a server-side request). If you can provide more details around reproduction or data to show that this is indeed a server-side issue, that would be appreciated.
